tmeta/records_outline.rs:114), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:353)). That’s easy to misuse and makes call sites know storage-order semantics. Use an enum or split helpers like `latest_transcript_records_by_hash` / `earliest_transcript_records_by_hash`.\n\n- **P4: `RecordDetail` makes the CLI JSON contract provider/storage-shaped.**  \n  [RecordDetail](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/records_outline.rs:30) exposes `tool_input: Value` and raw `source_record: Value` ([line 41](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/records_outline.rs:41)). That may be intentional for “full records,” but it’s a strong API promise: consumers will couple to transcript/provider payload shape. If this command is meant as a stable generic primitive, prefer a named envelope around raw payloads so the raw fields are clearly best-effort/unstable.\n\n**Note**\nI couldn’t read the external handoff doc from `IMPLEMENTATION-NOTES.md`; macOS denied access. I reviewed only the repo changes and nearby module patterns.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T20:50:19.997Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}